---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="How to Explore the Knowledge Commons" description="A guide to navigating the Bioregional Knowledge Commons">
  <main style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem 1.5rem;">
    <header style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-family:var(--mono);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.75rem 0;">
        <a href={`${base}/`} style="color:var(--muted);">Bioregional Knowledge Commons</a>
      </p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);font-weight:500;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--fg);font-family:var(--serif);letter-spacing:-0.01em;">How to explore the Knowledge Commons</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);margin:0;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.6;">
        <a href={`${base}/organizations`} style="color:var(--primary);">Organizations</a> · <a href={`${base}/ontology`} style="color:var(--primary);">Ontology</a> · <a href={`${base}/sources`} style="color:var(--primary);">Sources</a> · <a href={`${base}/how-to-explore`} style="color:var(--primary);">How to Explore the Knowledge Commons</a>
      </p>
    </header>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.65;">
        This knowledge base is made of three interconnected sections. Here's what each one is for and how to move between them.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--fg);font-family:var(--sans);">Organizations</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 1rem 0;">
        Organizations is the best place to start. You'll land on a world map — each pin is an organization working in bioregional or regenerative practice somewhere in the world.
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 1rem 0;">
        The map includes bioregionally oriented organizations, full case studies with detailed background and activities, and support organizations and learning networks that enable or connect bioregional work.
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">
        Click any pin on the map to open a side panel with the organization's details, or click the name in the table below to open its full page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--fg);font-family:var(--sans);">Ontology</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 1rem 0;">
        Ontology is the shared vocabulary of the Knowledge Commons — the concepts and themes that cut across all the organizations. Think of it as a thematic index: if you're curious about a topic like governance, finance, or land stewardship, start here. Each concept links to the organizations and activities related to it.
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">
        There are two layers: themes and tags. The themes are broad topics that contain lots of different tags. You can see the full list of themes below. Click on the arrows on the left to uncover each theme's tags.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--fg);font-family:var(--sans);">Sources</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">
        Sources is the bibliography — reports, essays, talks, and resources connected to the organizations and themes across this knowledge base. A good place to go deeper on something that caught your attention.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-bottom:2rem;padding:1.5rem;background:var(--surface);border-radius:var(--radius);border:1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 1rem 0;color:var(--fg);font-family:var(--sans);">A few things worth knowing</h2>
      <ul style="color:var(--fg);font-size:1rem;line-height:1.65;margin:0;padding-left:1.2rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">This knowledge base runs on Notion, a tool that organises information in interconnected tables. You don't need to know how it works — just click what interests you and use the back arrow to return. If you ever feel lost, the links at the top of any page will bring you back to the main sections.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Not every organization has a full case study yet — the Knowledge Commons is a living project and some entries are more complete than others.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">If you have suggestions, know of work that should be here, want to collaborate, or are just curious about what's behind it, reach out at <a href="mailto:yo@andreaisa.com" style="color:var(--primary);">yo@andreaisa.com</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:2rem;">
      <a href={`${base}/organizations`} style="display:inline-block;padding:0.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:var(--radius);background:var(--primary);color:var(--primary-fg);font-size:0.85rem;text-decoration:none;font-family:var(--mono);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;">
        Explore Organizations →
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/`} style="display:inline-block;padding:0.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:var(--radius);color:var(--muted);font-size:0.85rem;text-decoration:none;font-family:var(--mono);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;">
        ← Back to Dashboard
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
